              "content": "# The RAM Model of Computation — Understanding Growth Rates\nimport time\n\ndef measure_runtime(func, n):\n    \"\"\"Measure execution time for a given input size\"\"\"\n    data = list(range(n))\n    start = time.perf_counter()\n    func(data)\n    return time.perf_counter() - start\n\n# Different complexity classes grow very differently\nsizes = [10, 100, 1000, 10000]\nprint(\"Input size → O(1)  O(log n)  O(n)  O(n log n)  O(n²)\")\nprint(\"-\" * 55)\n\n# O(1): constant — always fast\n# O(log n): logarithmic — grows slowly\n# O(n): linear — proportional to input\n# O(n log n): linearithmic — typical for good sorts\n# O(n²): quadratic — slows quickly with input"
